qas.question: What is the EC-130H used for by the US Air Force?
What does the USAF use the E-4B aircraft for?

context: The purpose of electronic warfare is to <a0_0>deny the opponent an advantage in the EMS<a0_0/> and ensure friendly, unimpeded access to the EM spectrum portion of the information environment. Electronic warfare aircraft are used <a2_0>to keep airspaces friendly, and send critical information to anyone who needs it<a2_0/>. They are often called "<a1_0>The Eye in the Sky<a1_0/>." The roles of the aircraft vary greatly among the different variants to include <a3_0>Electronic Warfare/Jamming<a3_0/> (EC-130H), Psychological Operations/Communications (EC-130J), Airborne Early Warning and Control (E-3), <a4_0>Airborne Command Post<a4_0/> (E-4B), ground targeting radar (E-8C), range control (E-9A), and communications relay (E-11A)
